00:01:45.639 --> 00:01:47.339
I really do think the one
thing you should take away

00:01:47.339 --> 00:01:49.499
from curvature is the idea that

00:01:49.499 --> 00:01:51.606
it's the derivative of
the unit-tangent vector

00:01:51.606 --> 00:01:53.039
with respect to arc length

00:01:53.039 --> 00:01:54.139
and if you need to, you can just look up

00:01:54.139 --> 00:01:57.040
a formula like this but
it's worth pointing out

00:01:57.040 --> 00:01:58.820
that it makes some things easier

00:01:58.820 --> 00:02:00.320
to compute because
finding the tangent vector

00:02:00.320 --> 00:02:02.356
and everything can be
kind of like reinventing

00:02:02.356 --> 00:02:05.019
the wheel when you already
have the results here.

00:02:05.019 --> 00:02:07.012
So, first thing to do is just find

00:02:07.012 --> 00:02:09.578
x prime, y double-prime,

00:02:09.578 --> 00:02:11.339
y prime and x double prime.

00:02:11.339 --> 00:02:13.719
So let's go ahead and write those out.

00:02:13.719 --> 00:02:16.519
So the first derivative of x of t

00:02:16.519 --> 00:02:18.719
if we go up here that's t minus sine of t.

00:02:18.719 --> 00:02:22.302
So its derivative is
one minus cosine of t.

00:02:25.659 --> 00:02:27.359
And the derivative of the y component

00:02:27.359 --> 00:02:29.879
of one minus cosine t,

00:02:29.879 --> 00:02:30.962
y prime of t,

00:02:32.458 --> 00:02:36.900
is gonna be, derivative
of cosine is negative sine

00:02:36.900 --> 00:02:38.940
so negative derivative of that is sine,

00:02:38.940 --> 00:02:42.339
and that one goes to a constant,

00:02:42.339 --> 00:02:46.560
and then when we take the second
derivatives of those guys,

00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:49.240
so maybe change the color for
the second derivative here,

00:02:49.240 --> 00:02:51.073
x double prime of the,

00:02:52.659 --> 00:02:54.819
so now we're taking
the derivative of this,

00:02:54.819 --> 00:02:55.959
which actually we just did because

00:02:55.959 --> 00:02:57.979
by coincidence the first derivative of x

00:02:57.979 --> 00:03:00.097
is also the y component

00:03:00.097 --> 00:03:02.597
so that also equals sine of t.

00:03:04.639 --> 00:03:08.806
And then y double prime is just
the derivative of sine here

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:13.867
so that's just gonna
be cosine, cosine of t.

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:17.620
So now, when we just
plug those four values

00:03:17.620 --> 00:03:21.405
in for kappa, for our
curvature, what we get

00:03:21.405 --> 00:03:24.738
is x prime was one minus cosine of t,

00:03:28.940 --> 00:03:32.614
multiplied by y double
prime is cosine of t.

00:03:32.614 --> 00:03:33.614
Cosine of t.

00:03:34.939 --> 00:03:36.900
We subtract off from that y prime,

00:03:36.900 --> 00:03:39.249
which is sine of t,

00:03:39.249 --> 00:03:40.082
sine of t,

00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:43.800
multiplied by x double prime.

00:03:43.800 --> 00:03:45.960
So x double prime is also sine of t,

00:03:45.960 --> 00:03:47.900
so I could just say

00:03:47.900 --> 00:03:49.576
sine of t squared,

00:03:49.576 --> 00:03:53.743
and the whole thing is
divided by x prime squared

00:03:54.620 --> 00:03:57.953
so x prime was one minus cosine of t,

00:04:00.020 --> 00:04:01.700
minus cosine of t,

00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:04.117
squared, plus y prime squared

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:06.300
so y prime was just sine,

00:04:06.300 --> 00:04:10.583
so that's just gonna be sine squared of t.

00:04:10.583 --> 00:04:14.500
And that whole thing to
the power three halves.

00:04:15.859 --> 00:04:17.580
And that's your answer, right?

00:04:17.580 --> 00:04:19.720
You apply the formula, you get the answer.

